使用軟體

  Audition 

  

  Audiomulch 

  

   GRM plug ins

  

MSP

  

Audition 簡介

0 Start Audition--練習a.多音軌視窗(Multitrack
view)與b.編輯視窗(Edit view)之切換(Keyboard 8 change to b, 9 to a 或滑鼠選定)。



1開啟聲音檔(Auto Play 試聽 before open)--左下圖多音軌視窗--於右下圖中選取1= open file(2 =close file)，中選取Auto 試聽 after open。 




2置放聲音檔於音軌—以滑鼠選定音軌置放聲音處--中先選取聲音—選3=insert to multitrack (或直接以滑鼠拖曳拉入音軌中)



3編輯聲音檔—選4=Edit
file

        


---------------------------------------------------------------------













4 熟悉更多功能面版 :



1=音量線 
2 =左右聲道線 
3=1與2調線方格  4=常用工具  5=搬動複製    6=組織器  7=混音器 8=等化器  9=撥放  10=大小縮放   11=時間  12=撥放音量  13= 影像

---------------------------------------------------------------------

       

音軌之R、 S 、M 顯示-- R=Record, S=Solo, M=Mute,V=Volume,
P=Pan, H,M,L= high,middle,low frequency         


---------------------------------------------------------------------

重要: 在音軌之波形上，按滑鼠右鍵搬動音軌 

Loop Duplicate--複製許多copy, Clip Color 改變聲音片段顏色

Convert into unique
copy (轉換獨特copy)--使變化該聲音時不會改變原本母體聲---------------------------------------------------------------------

推薦功能:

** Edit View—Effects-Time/pitch—Stretch-Gliding
stretching 

** Effects—Special—Music


**Edit—Mix Paste 

---------------------------------------------------------------------存檔: File-Save Session As，下次用Open Session開檔。。  

**若是在不同電腦上操作，存檔於隨身碟時不忘打勾於Save copies of all Associated Files，才能儲存Everything              

---------------------------------------------------------------------

混音:
--Edit-Mix Down to File-All Waves 

FOR CD音軌(Audio Track)燒錄 --混音成**.wav

!! 在Audition 軟體上直接燒錄—至 CD Project View—拉入混好聲音—Write CD

FOR USB儲存--混音成**.wav 或 **mp3  

Acoustics and DSP Find
out the Meanings of the following Terms: 

Wave Length                         Cycle

Period                              Frequency

Pitch                               Hertz   

Ultrasonic                          Infrasonic

Amplitude                          Intensity

Loudness                            dB

Envelope                           Attack 

Sustain                             Decay

Noise                               Musical Sound 

White Noise                        Pink
Noise

Spectrum                           Timbre(Tone
Color)

Harmonics                              Inharmonics

Partials                            Overtones

Tone                                Note

Waveform                            Sine
Wave 

Square wave                         Sawtooth                    

Equal Loudness Contour              
Phase



Delay                               Echo 

Reverb                              EQ

LP Filtering                        HP Filtering

BP Filtering                        BR Filtering

Panning                             Doppler 

Pitch Bending                       Time Stretch 

Normalizing                         Sampling Rate

Quantization Error                  Phase Cancellation 

Beating                             ADC


DAC                                 Nyquist
frequence 

Alias                               FM Synthesis

Additive
Synthesis                  Subtractive
Synthesis    













